Check whether a given String 'S' is a palindrome using recursion.


Return true or false.


Note:
You donâ€™t need to print anything. Just implement the given function.
Example:
Input: s = "racecar"
Output: true
Explanation: "racecar" is a palindrome.
Input Format:
The first and only line of the input contains string S.
Output format:
Return a boolean value True or False.





public class Solution {
    public static boolean isPalindrome(String str) {
        // Write your code here.
         return (isStringPalindrome(str,0,str.length()-1));
	}
    
    public static boolean isStringPalindrome(String str, int si, int ei)
    {
        if (si>=ei)
        {
            return true;
        }
        boolean check=true;
        if (str.charAt(si)==str.charAt(ei))
        {
            check=isStringPalindrome(str,si+1,ei-1);
        }
        else
        {
            check=false;
        }
        return check;
    
    }
}
